  "response": "Pakistani views towards India are complex and varied, but generally characterized by:\n\n1. Historical tensions\n- Ongoing Kashmir conflict\n- Multiple wars since 1947 partition\n- Territorial disputes\n\n2. Political perspectives\n- Often perceive India as a strategic threat\n- Critical of India's policies towards Muslims\n- Rivalry in regional geopolitics\n\n3. Cultural attitudes\n- Some share historical cultural connections\n- Mutual respect for shared language and traditions\n- Mistrust due to historical conflicts\n\n4. Common perceptions\n- Many view India negatively due to political differences\n- Concern about India's military and economic power\n- Some younger generations desire improved relations\n\n5. Diverse opinions\n- Urban, educated Pakistanis might have more nuanced views\n- Rural populations often hold stronger nationalist sentiments\n- Individual perspectives vary widely\n\n6. Media influence\n- National media often portrays India negatively\n- Sensationalist reporting affects public perception\n\n7. People-to-people connections\n- Some desire cultural exchange and peaceful relations\n- Family connections across border\n- Shared entertainment industries\n\nThese perspectives are generalizations, and individual Pakistani opinions can differ significantly based on personal experiences, education, and background.",
